    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Keyed monochords developed in France in the 1880s, having an oval body, 29 keys set on the neck, and a single string made of horsehair.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
